metadata.description:
B95, nicknamed moonbird, is a red knot (a species of shorebird in the sandpiper family) celebrated for its longevity as the oldest known member of its species. This collection of unique pieces was inspired by this famous bird.

This work is a derivative of Chuck Homler d/b/a Focus On Wildlife, CC BY-SA 4.0 <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0>, via Wikimedia Commons
